Table Caption:
Chemical composition of as-cast carbon-doped Fe40.4Ni11.3Mn34.8Al7.5Cr6 HEAs (denoted as Cx, where x is the carbon concentration) determined using ASTM E1019 and ASTM
E1621 test procedures by Chicago Spectro Service Laboratory, Inc, Chicago, IL (in at. %).

Yield stress, ultimate tensile stress (UTS), elongation to fracture and strain hardening rate (SHR) for Fe40.4Ni11.3Mn34.8Al7.5Cr6 HEAs with the various amounts of carbon (denoted as Cx, where x is the carbon concentration) are shown. The error bars indicate the standard deviation calculated from three tests.
The corrected partial dislocation spacing (dc) and the dislocation character angle (b) of the undoped, 0.07 at. % carbon-doped and 1.1 at. % carbon-doped HEAs based on measurements from WBDF images.
